The paper presents an algorithm for testing 3-edge-connectivity in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and graph algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) or "Computational Geometry" (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the computation and certification of 3-edge-connected components and 2-cuts, which are related to graph partitioning and network analysis, suggesting that it could also belong to the categories of "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM) or "Graph Theory" (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the computation of 3-vertex-connected components, which is a problem in network analysis and connectivity, indicating that it could also belong to the category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
